  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ASSISTANT BUILDING CONSTRUCTION ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage and operate all construction equipments and power hand tools.</li>\n  <li>Provide assistance to all processes in emergency outages and administer efficient      flow of all work.</li>\n  <li>Prepare shop-drawings and follow-up on subsequent comments.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge on Autocad is prefered.</li>\n  <li>Attend project safety meeting and site co-ordination meeting.</li>\n  <li>Schedule and arrange site access arrangement for delivery with main contractor.</li>\n  <li>Monitor materials delivery schedule.</li>\n  <li>Monitor daily work progress and feedback.</li>\n  <li>Implement variation work upon receiving new drawings and instructions</li>\n  <li>Conduct follow up site testing.</li>\n  <li>Commissioning of project in line with main contractor's timeline</li>\n  <li>Prepare as-built drawings,operation and maintenance manual.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>REQUIREMENTS :</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>*Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent.</p>\n<p>*Able to design and calculate the strength of the structure independently.</p>\n<p>*Familiarity with design software (eg. Autodesk, AutoCad Civil 3D, and MicroStation)</p>\n<p>Knowledge of map creation software and photo imaging software</p>\n<p>*Strong Analytical and critical thinking skills with high level of accuracy in calculations and design</p>\n<p>*Good interpersonal skills, positive attitude and pro-active</p>\n<p>*Willing to work day and night</p>\n<p>*To comply with the policies and procedures of the company.</p>\n<p>*Long term commitment</p>\n<p>*Possesses local Class 3 and/or Class 4 driving license an added advantage</p>\n<p>*Ability to coordinate more than one project at a time</p>",
